So well known is the present work, now for the first time printed, from the extensive and admirable use made of it by the late Mr. VVay in his edition of the ‘Promptorium Par- vulorum,’ that it can require little or no introduction to the , students of our language beyond that given by Mr. Wheatley in his Preface. I will, therefore, confine myself to an expla- nation of the plan and principles of this edition, with a very few remarks on the MSS. and their dialect and peculiarities.
